---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Nurse AI Notes"
	description="Why this blog exists and how content is reviewed"
	pubDate={new Date('March 01 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Nurse AI Notes is an educational blog focused on how artificial intelligence intersects with real
		nursing work. We write for student nurses preparing for practice and for licensed nurses who want
		clear, practical guidance without hype.
	</p>

	<p>
		Our goal is to help readers answer three questions before adopting any AI tool:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Is it clinically useful for this task?</li>
		<li>Is it safe and compliant with policy, privacy, and documentation standards?</li>
		<li>Is it equitable for diverse patient populations and care settings?</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		You can expect content on bedside workflows, nursing education, quality improvement, leadership,
		and ethics. We emphasize examples that fit common nursing environments such as med-surg, ICU,
		community health, and outpatient care.
	</p>

	<p>
		When possible, posts include references to nursing competencies, evidence-based practice principles,
		and implementation realities such as staffing constraints, alert fatigue, and change management.
	</p>

	<p>
		Nothing on this site is individualized medical advice. Always follow your local policy, scope of
		practice, and preceptor or manager guidance before applying recommendations in patient care.
	</p>
</Layout>
